  "prompt": "Will yongnuo RF 603 ii RF triggers allows High speed sync triggering?",
  "response": "The Yongnuo RF-603 II triggers **do not support High-Speed Sync (HSS)**. The RF-603 II is primarily designed for basic wireless flash triggering and operates in manual mode, which means it doesn't have the capability to handle the additional communication required for HSS.\n\n**High-Speed Sync** allows your camera to use shutter speeds faster than the camera\u2019s native sync speed (typically around 1/200s to 1/250s) by effectively pulsing the flash rapidly to illuminate the scene throughout the entire duration of the shutter's movement. To utilize HSS, both your camera and flash system, as well as the triggering device, must support this feature.\n\nIf HSS is essential for your photography needs, consider upgrading to more advanced trigger systems within Yongnuo's lineup that explicitly support HSS, such as:\n\n- **Yongnuo YN-622C/YN-622N**: These triggers offer TTL functionality and support HSS, making them suitable for more advanced lighting setups.\n- **Yongnuo YN-560-TX**: This is another option that provides wireless control with HSS capabilities.\n\nBefore purchasing, always verify the compatibility of the triggers with your specific camera and flash units to ensure full functionality.\n\n**In summary:** The Yongnuo RF-603 II does not support High-Speed Sync. For HSS capabilities, you\u2019ll need to look into more advanced triggering systems like the YN-622 series or other compatible models that explicitly offer HSS support.",
